  <div class="info-intro">
    <div class="intro-container">
      <p>Poison Ivy, Oak, and Sumac grow almost everywhere in the United States except Alaska, Hawaii, and some parts of Nevada. 85% of people are allergic, up to 15% are extremely allergic, and 50 million American get the rash caused by these plants every year.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="intro-container">
      <p>These plants all have an oily mixture called urushiol that causes a rash by sticking to your skin, clothing, and tools. The rash takes around two weeks to heal.
<br><br>Luckily, Aitex can remove this oily mixture that is tough to wash off!</p>
    </div>
